  <section>
    <h2>Progressive Enhancement</h2>
    <p>Without JavaScript, the fallback content (whatever HTML is inside the element) remains visible. The <code>src</code> URL is never fetched, so users see the fallback. This makes it safe to use for non-critical content.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fallback content ensures content is always available.</li>
      <li>Error state shows a message when content fails to load (unless fallback content exists).</li>
      <li>Changing the <code>src</code> attribute triggers a re-fetch, enabling dynamic content updates.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

